In article <765288907snz@bell.demon.co.uk> Peter@bell.demon.co.uk writes:
>
>I was looking at the DES, and wondered if the initial and final permutations
>actually have any effect on the strength of the cypher.

at crypto '93, one of the talks pointed out that the initial
permutation makes it harder to use differential cryptanalysis
against cipher-feedback mode des. the reference is:

preneel, nuttin, rijmen, buelens, cryptanalysis of des in the cfb mode.
proceedings of crypto '93. springer verlag.

						-don davis, openvision
